<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col s12 m12">
      <h1 class="header center <%=public._data.baseColor %>-text">Registration</h1>
      <h3 class="header center light">Create a JSON File and submit it via a GitHub Pull Request</h3>
    <div class="center">
      <p>To register for JS CrafCamp you have to add a json file with your name and some other information to our <a href="https://github.com/jscraftcamp/website" target="_blank">GitHub Repository</a> via a
        <a href="http://stackoverflow.com/questions/14680711/how-to-do-a-github-pull-request" target="_blank">Pull Request</a>. Registration is free of charge.
        Your json file should follow the naming scheme <code>$firstname_$lastname.json</code> and must be placed in the folder <code>participants</code>. The structure of the file is described below.</p>
      <p>To test if your json file is a valid registration you can run <code>npm test</code> (more details about this are in the <a href="https://github.com/jscraftcamp/website/blob/master/README.md" target="_blank">README</a>). Invalid registrations will be rejected.</p>
      <p>Out of these files a page with information about <a href="/participants.html">all participants</a> is generated.</p>
      <p>To unregister please write another pull request or <a href="mailto:team@jscraftcamp.org">let us know</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col s12 m12">
      <h4 class="header center blue-text">The JSON Format</h4>
      <pre data-line="2,4,5,6-9" class="language-json">
      <code class="language-json">
        {
          "name": "Foo Bar",
          "company": "A company name",
          "tags": [ "angular" ],
          "when": {
            "friday": true,
            "friday_party": true,
            "saturday": true
          },
          "what_is_my_connection_to_javascript": "Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit.",
          "what_can_i_contribute": "Ut enim ad minim veniam, quis nostrud exercitation ullamco laboris.",
          "tshirt": "W-S",
          "urls": {
            "photo": "http://materializecss.com/images/sample-1.jpg",
            "homepage": "http://www.example.com/",
            "github": "https://github.com/",
            "twitter": "https://twitter.com/"
          }
        }
      </code>
      </pre>
    </div>
    <div class="col s12 m10">
      <table class="bordered">
        <tr><td><code>name</code>*</td>		<td>first name and last name or a nick name</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>company</code></td>	<td>A company name</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>tags</code>*</td>		<td>(JavaScript related) topics you would like to show, speak or discuss about</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>when.friday</code>*</td>	<td>If you are attending on Friday (Boolean value)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>when.friday_party</code>*</td>	<td>If you want to join us on the free Party that will happen Friday after the event (same location). Drinks and food sponsored!</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>when.saturday</code>*</td><td>If you are attending on Saturday (Boolean value)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>what_is_my_connection_to_javascript</code>*</td><td> 2-5 sentences about your experience with JavaScript or related technologies.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>what_can_i_contribute</code></td><td>1-3 sentences about what you would like to contribute to the BarCamp.</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>tshirt</code></td>	<td>We will have a limited number of t-shirts with the event and sponsor logos. If you want one: fit (W=women, M=Man) and size (S,M,L,XL), e.g. W-S or M-XL. </td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>urls.photo</code></td>	<td>URL to a photo of you</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>urls.homepage</code></td>	<td>URL to your homepage</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>urls.github</code></td>	<td>URL to your GitHub Account</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>urls.twitter</code></td>	<td>URL to your Twitter Account</td></tr>
      </table>
      <p>*: mandatory field</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

